Reasoning: 
1. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with multi-agent systems with continuous-time dynamics and proposes a distributed control rule to achieve consensus and optimal agreement. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper explicitly mentions multi-agent systems and their optimization problem. The proposed algorithm is also a distributed one, which is a common theme in multi-agent systems research.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes a decentralized continuous-time algorithm for solving the intersection computation problem. This falls under the scope of distributed computing.
4. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper deals with an optimization problem where each component is only known to a particular node. The proposed algorithm aims to achieve an optimal agreement within the optimal solution set of the overall optimization objective.
5. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper uses convex and non-smooth analysis to establish several important properties of the distance functions with respect to the global optimal solution set and a class of invariant sets. This falls under the scope of numerical analysis.
